                      NPC Behavior: Chat Behavior
                      ===========================

Description
-----------

The load_chat and load_a_chat functionality has been subsumed by the
generic chat behavior. While load_chat and load_a_chat still function,
they have been deprecated and it is suggested that you use the new API
directly. load_chat strings will be active while the NPC is in a 
resting state, and load_a_chat strings will be active while the NPC is
in a fighting state.

Chat strings can have a set of states for which they are active. These 
states correspond to the general behavior states and are defined in 
<npcstates.h>. A chat string will have the chance to be selected for
output whenever the NPC is in a state for which the chat string is
registered.

The NPC will now only have a single chat % chance, as opposed to a 
separate chance for normal and attack strings.


NPC Chat API
------------

void set_chat_chance(int chance)
- Set the % chance for a chat string to be output.

void add_chat(string str, int state)
- Register a chat string for a set of states as in <npcstate.h>.

object query_chat_behavior()
- Return the chat behavior object for further customization.


NPC Chat Behavior API
---------------------

The chat behavior object can also be manipulated directly:

varargs void add_chat(string msg, int states)
- Adds a chat string to the behavior for a set of states. 

void set_chance(int chance)
- Sets the chat chance.

int get_chance()
- Returns the chat chance.


